article.description: Micah Bradford came off the bench to score a career-high 20 points and lead Valparaiso to an 88-46 win over Division III North Park in the season opener Friday night.
article.headline: Bradford's 20 leads Valparaiso past North Park, 88-46
article.linkText: Bradford's 20 leads Valparaiso past North Park, 88-46
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Micah Bradford came off the bench to score a career-high 20 points and lead Valparaiso to an 88-46 win over Division III North Park in the season opener Friday night. The Crusaders held the Division III Vikings scoreless for more than 10 minutes to start the game, opening with a 15-0 run, and built a 23-point advantage after the first 20 minutes to lead 40-17 at intermission. Valparaiso also held North Park scoreless for more than five minutes in the second half. Bradford, who hit 8 of 12 shots from the field, including 2 of 6 from distance, did all his scoring in 16 minutes of playing time. Markus Golder had 12 points and 10 boards for Valparaiso, which now has won 13 straight home openers. Jason Hines was the lone North Park shooter to reach double figures, finishing with 13 points.
